    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.8.0-dev-817-g33b77eb72\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.25.2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\nRun\r\n```sh\r\nnvim --clean -c 'lua vim.defer_fn(function() end, 0)' -c quit\r\n```\r\nor run `nvim --clean` and source this Lua file:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.defer_fn(function()\r\nend, 0)\r\nvim.cmd('quit')\r\n\r\n```\r\nwith ASAN\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo leak of luv handles\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n2 seconds hang on exit because of leaked luv handles",
